weeks pregnant and so deppressed im weeks pregnant with my second pregnancy i was pregnant last year and this week last year i lost my daughter at weeks gestation and the doctors still cant tell me why her heart stopped with this second pregnancy my due date is days after my previous due date last year and it just seems like the world is out to get me im tring to keep stress away from me but its coming at me sooo fast all i want to do is scream and cry first the timing of this pregnancy and my last is so hard to deal with then my husband gets laid off from work and we loose our insurance finally after a huge ordeal we get on state aid and now im tring to plan my baby shower and my invites that i ordered on ebay are lost in the mail and my shower is sept i know my hormones are going crazy but i just want to cry i feel like i need antideppressants but my doctor wont prescribe me any and i dont know what to do anymore i know this isnt a question but i need to talk to soemone who has had any kindof break down during there pregnancy and how they kept there cool when things started to fall apart around them did your baby come out ok still even though the stress levels were so high i really want my baby and i want to do whatever i can to make sure shes healthy but i cant take this anymore i too lost a baby my little girl was weeks gestation my son was concieved a couple years later and all the grieving i thought was over wasn't it was a real struggle for me too when i got to that point in my pregnancy i would wake up hysterical thinking i had lost him too it was truly a rollercoaster of emotions wanting to enjoy it but being afraid to just in case something happened to him too i honestly felt like i was coming unglued i got teary just reading your painful struggle so from one mom to another a big hug for you but one thing that did help me suggested by my ob was a vitamin supplement for inositol its a b vit and it helped so much with the racing thoughts the ups and downs and the anxiety no it didnt take away the pain i still to this day miss my hannah but it did help me to cope and gave me back the ability to enjoy my pregnancy without feeling guilty i took i t x a day and it really helped me calm down with out taking regular meds i was still a little scared doing kick counts every hour but i did make it and i hope that this is able to be a happy event in your lives so keep taking your prenatals get plenty of sleep eat as healthy as you can and get a bit of exercise if you are up to it adn please make sure you discuss all this with your ob and watch out for post partum too you can email me or message me if you want tarheelgirl take care Pregnancy Obstetrics Breastfeeding Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Knots Landing Childbirth Urinary incontinence Miscarriage Abortion debate Friends Jon Secada Abortion Clinical depression Chronic fatigue syndrome Prostate cancer Attention-deficit hyperactivity disorder Charmed Kodocha Postpartum depression Hormone replacement therapy (trans) The Ashlee Simpson Show Cindy Sheehan Neighbours Shaggy dog story Infantilism Avenue Q Everwood Fertility awareness Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Transsexuality Days of our Lives Jam (TV series) Tocopherol Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma Folic acid Bipolar disorder The Contender (television series) Theory of conduct Sharon Tate Psoriasis Humphrey Bogart The Amber Spyglass Wild at Heart (Buffy episode) Milton H. Erickson Phoebe Halliwell The Catcher in the Rye Spice Girls Elvis and Me Elephant The Apprentice 2 T'Pol Menstrual cycle The Inside Social rule Panic attack Hypertension Scientology beliefs and practices History of As the World Turns (2000-present) Stillbirth The Lion, the Witch and the Wardrobe Stomach cancer Ron and Fez Characters in the Smurfs Father's Day (Doctor Who) Diabetes mellitus Eddie Guerrero Fecal incontinence Guinea pig Characters of Lost The Lovely Bones One Tree Hill (TV series) Abortion in the United States Miss Saigon Kurt Cobain Sigmu